1 point or button must be used instead of a square. Except as expressly
2 authorized or required by statute, a county election board may not print
3 a ballot label that contains language concerning the public question
4 other than the language authorized by a statute.
5 (o) The requirements in this section:
6 (1) do not replace; and
7 (2) are in addition to;
8 any other requirements in this title that apply to ballots for electronic
9 voting systems.
10 (p) The procedure described in IC 3-11-2-16 must be used when a
11 ballot label does not comply with the requirements imposed by this title
12 or contains another error or omission that might result in confusion or
13 mistakes by voters.
14 SECTION 10. IC 3-11-14-14.5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.195-2025,
15 SECTION 13, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
16 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 14.5. A ballot label must not include a touch
17 sensitive point or button to permit a voter to cast a straight party ticket
18 for a political party if:
19 (1) there are no candidates of that political party; or
20 (2) the only candidates:
21 (A) of the political party; or
22 (B) that have stated an affiliation with the political party under
23 IC 3-8-2.5-2.5(a)(5);
24 are for election to school board offices or offices to which more
25 than one (1) individual is to be elected and which will not be
26 credited with a vote under IC 3-12-1-7 or IC 3-12-1-7.1 if a voter
27 casts a straight party ticket.
28 SECTION 11. IC 3-12-1-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.195-2025,
29 SECTION 14, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
30 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) This subsection does not apply to a ballot
31 card voting system or an electronic voting system. Except as provided
32 in subsection (d), a voting mark made by a voter on or in a voting
33 square at the left of a candidate's name or political party's name shall
34 be counted as a vote for the candidate or candidates of the political
35 party.
36 (b) This subsection applies to a ballot card voting system. A voting
37 mark made by a voter:
38 (1) on or in a circle, oval, or square; or
39 (2) to connect a connectable arrow;
40 immediately below or beside a candidate's name or political party's
41 name shall be counted as a vote for the candidate or candidates of the
42 political party, except as provided in subsection (d).
2026 IN 1377—LS 6830/DI 144

15
1 (c) This subsection applies to a direct record electronic voting
2 system. A voting mark made by a voter touching a touch sensitive point
3 or button below or beside a candidate's name or political party's name
4 shall be counted as a vote for the candidate or candidates of the
5 political party, except as provided in subsection (d).
6 (d) A voter who wishes to cast a ballot for a candidate for election
7 to a school board office or an at-large district to which more than one
8 (1) person may be elected on a:
9 (1) county council;
10 (2) city common council;
11 (3) town council; or
12 (4) township board;
13 must make a voting mark for each individual candidate for whom the
14 voter wishes to cast a vote. A straight ticket voting mark on a paper
15 ballot, ballot card voting system, or electronic voting system shall not
16 be counted as a straight party ticket voting mark as a vote for any
17 candidate for an a school board office. described by this subsection.
18 SECTION 12. IC 3-12-1-7, AS AMENDED BY P.L.21-2016,
19 SECTION 23, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
20 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) This subsection applies whenever a voter:
21 (1) votes a straight party ticket; and
22 (2) votes only for one (1) or more individual candidates who are
23 all of the same political party as the straight ticket vote.
24 Except as provided in subsection (d), or (e), the straight ticket vote
25 shall be counted and the individual candidate votes may not be
26 counted.
27 (b) This subsection applies whenever:
28 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
29 one (1) political party;
30 (2) only one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
31 (3) the voter has voted for one (1) individual candidate for the
32 office described in subdivision (2) who is:
33 (A) a candidate of a political party other than the party for
34 which the voter voted a straight ticket; or
35 (B) an independent candidate or declared write-in candidate
36 for the office.
37 If the voter has voted for one (1) individual candidate for the office
38 described in subdivision (2), the individual candidate vote for that
39 office shall be counted, the straight party ticket vote for that office may
40 not be counted, and the straight party ticket votes for other offices on
41 the ballot shall be counted.
42 (c) This subsection applies whenever:
2026 IN 1377—LS 6830/DI 144

16
1 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
2 one (1) political party; and
3 (2) the voter has voted for more individual candidates for the
4 office than the number of persons to be elected to that office.
5 The individual candidate votes for that office may not be counted, the
6 straight party ticket vote for that office may not be counted, and the
7 straight party ticket votes for other offices on the ballot shall be
8 counted.
9 (d) This subsection applies whenever:
10 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
11 one (1) political party;
12 (2) more than one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
13 (3) the voter has voted for one (1) or more individual candidates
14 for the office described in subdivision (2) who are:
15 (A) independent candidates or declared write-in candidates;
16 (B) candidates of a political party other than the political party
17 for which the voter cast a straight party ticket under
18 subdivision (1); or
19 (C) candidates of the same political party for which the
20 voter cast a straight party ticket under subdivision (1); or
21 (C) (D) a combination of candidates described in clauses (A),
22 and (B), and (C).
23 The individual votes cast by the voter for the office for the independent
24 candidates, declared write-in candidates, and the candidates of a
25 political party other than the political party for which the voter cast a
26 straight party ticket shall be counted unless the total number of these
27 individual votes is greater than the number of persons to be elected to
28 the office. The straight party ticket votes for the office shall not be
29 counted. The straight party ticket votes for other offices on the voter's
30 ballot shall be counted.
31 (e) This subsection applies whenever:
32 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
33 one (1) political party;
34 (2) more than one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
35 (3) the voter has voted for individual candidates for the office
36 described in subdivision (2) who are:
37 (A) independent candidates, declared write-in candidates, or
38 candidates of a political party other than the political party for
39 which the voter cast a straight party ticket under subdivision
40 (1); and
41 (B) candidates of the same political party for which the voter
42 cast a straight party ticket under subdivision (1).
